        <name>W4 Q03 Lagrange multiplier</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p&gt;Find the maximum and minimum values of \[f({@v1@},{@v2@})={@f@}\] subject to \[ {@C@}.\] Write the Lagrange function in the form \(f({@v1@},{@v2@}) - \lambda g({@v1@},{@v2@})\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;(a)&lt;/b&gt; For which values of \({@v1@}\) do critical points of \( f- \lambda g\) occur? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\( x = \) [[input:ansx]] [[validation:ansx]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;(b)&lt;/b&gt; The maximum/minimum of \(f({@v1@},{@v2@})={@f@}\) subject to \( {@C@}\) is&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(\mbox{max} = \) [[input:ansmax]] [[validation:ansmax]]&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(\mbox{min} = \) [[input:ansmin]] [[validation:ansmin]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;To find the maximum and minimum values of 
\[f({@v1@},{@v2@})={@f@}\] 
subject to \( {@C@}\) we use the method of Lagrange multipliers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In general we have the function \(f({@v1@},{@v2@})\) and the constraint \(g({@v1@},{@v2@}) = {@lhs(C)-rhs(C)@}=0\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We write \[ \phi({@v1@},{@v2@},\lambda) = f({@v1@},{@v2@})+\lambda\, g({@v1@},{@v2@}) = {@f@}+ \lambda ({@(lhs(C)-rhs(C))@})^{**}\]
and then solve
\[ \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial{@v1@}} = {@DP1@}=0\]
\[ \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial{@v2@}} = {@DP2@}=0\]
\[ \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial {@l@}} = {@DPl@}=0\]
This gives us three equations in three unknowns, \( {@v1@},{@v2@},{@l@}\), which can be solved to get:
\[ {@ssol@}.\]
Evaluating \(f\) at each of these points gives respective values as \( \left[{@tamax@}, {@tamin@} \right] \).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hence the minimum value is {@tamin@} and the maximum value is {@tamax@}.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\( ** \) Because we are using the variable \(l\) as part of the Maxima code we replace \( \lambda \) with \(l.\)&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
